			<DIV>Maddar_Xegony wrote<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
togam wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Maddar_Xegony wrote:<BR>Scenario for you Kahm, group is fighting in a Nest instance with no snarer or an absent minded one. A goblin starts running away at close to selos speed into a highly populated room. Warrior pops the suggested ability, snaring the mob to a near stop long enough for the group to kill it or for the snarer to actually get it snared. Now replace that warrior with a paladin, paladin casts root, root is broken within a second or two by a dd or resisted entirely, mob runs a bit, paladin tries root again but he has to wait 3 seconds (6 if he fizzles) and the mob has already aggroed the room, group dies. If you think that's an uncommon scenario....well it's not. Yes, root can used for cc'ing, that's in fact the only reliable function of it, but that's not what we're discussing. Giving warriors a snaring ability leaves paladins out tanked, out utilitied, and out dps'ed in most challenging single group content. You don't think that effects balance? The change has to be smaller and preferably applied across several classes if the warrior community wants it put into effect. 
<P>Message Edited by Maddar_Xegony on <SPAN class=date_text><FONT color=#ffffff>07-04-2005</FONT></SPAN> <FONT color=#ffffff><SPAN class=time_text>02:56 PM</SPAN><BR></FONT></P><FONT color=#ffffff>
<HR>
</FONT></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>wait wait , i wanna get this straight .</P>
<UL>
<LI>you have no snarer or an absent minded one . meaning you either didn't plan correctly or the people you are grouped with are incompetent ? 
<LI>i must assume that at least 2 other people in the group must have some sort of snare or mez, or root . 
<LI>mob is able to get far enough from a group to get adds . 
<LI>you believe " Giving warriors a snaring ability leaves paladins out tanked, out utilitied, and out dps'ed in most challenging single group content. "</LI></UL>
<P>groups or raids that don't plan right or have incompetent people are supposed to wipe . if you cannot root , there were at least 2 other people able to to back you up. you weren't clearing fast enough to keep the adds beat down , or if you were on initial clearing in , you didn't have an escape plan , which is poor planning . you actually believe giving warrior a utility function like stopping a runner makes warrior tank better , but paladin who already have runner stopping ability don't tank better because they have that ability . </P>
<P>
<HR>

<P></P>
<P>umm lets take a look at some of your later logic and perhaps you can explain that also . </P>
<P>% damage stun mitigated: 13.1%<BR>warriors innate - 1DI alone gives them a 5% mitigation boost over knights.</P>
<DIV>3 minutes at 50% reduction of the DI portion of melee damage only</DIV>
<DIV>10 minutes of normal Warrior mitigation</DIV>
<DIV>Average mitigation for the 13 minute period 11.54%</DIV>
<P>Obviously 13.1% is less than <STRONG>16.54%</STRONG> (11.54 + 5).</P>
<P>
<HR>

<P></P>
<P>13.1 &gt;11.54 maddar , the 5 % warrior mitigation is already factored into the equasion . <STRONG>note: you didn't use your own mitigation discipline while figuring your mitigation percentage , and you used an external slower </STRONG></P>
<P>circular logic at work here again maddar . </P>
<UL>
<LI>if you are right and stuns can mitigate 13.1 % dps , then warrior need an upgrade to make warrior mitigate greater than the 11.4 % bbz has shown . 
<LI>if you are wrong then stuns don't mitigate 13.1%dps . stuns will mitigate more than 13.1% so warrior need an even greater mitigation upgrade . 
<LI>
<DIV><STRONG>We are planning to do away with stun immune mobs.</STRONG></DIV>
<P><STRONG>Brenlo Bixiebopper<BR>Director of Community Relations</STRONG><STRONG><BR></STRONG><BR></P></LI></UL>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>No....no, the -1 DI was not already factored into the equation, if you want to argue that it isn't in effect while defensive is going, and it might not be, I didn't consider that, then the total would still be 15.38%.<BR><BR>You think stun mitigation will be in our favor? It's a plan to simultaneously nerf the effect of stun and deal with the problem of spells with a level cap no longer being castable on mobs over that cap. It does not mean all mobs will be stunnable, it means that stun will land on all mobs, and be mitigated 100%. </DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
