			<DIV>Ya know Maddar, we didn't mind too much explaining Shocking Defense to you nor why Hamstring in no way is anyway near as powerful as SK snares or root.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"First off, Battleblade's figures are in no way shape or form a parse. He based them off a very simple calculation."<BR>But explaining middle school math is a bit much:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Warrior innate mitigation includes "-1 DI"<STRONG> we are contrasting the beyond class <U>base</U> mitigation provided by "stun mitigation" and Defensive, not differences in innate mitigation.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A more accurate calculation would be:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3 minutes at 45% mitigation via Defensive (50% less the 5% innate warrior DI mitigation)</DIV>
<DIV>10 minutes at 0%</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10.38% mitigation of the DI potion of the damage only</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And even when cooking the number furiously, you neglect that Warrior damage taken is found in the formula -</DIV>
<DIV>Damage = DB + ( ( RND(20)*DI) * 0.95)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>completely ignoring the fact that Defensive is not a 45% reduction in melee damage taken, but <U>only in the DI contribution of the damage taken</U>. DB is never 0, and the average mitigation provided by Defensive is <U>always</U> less than 10.38%</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Seriously, everbody makes errors and assumptions especially when discussing another class. But you have an abysmal tendancy to cling to stuff when <U>both</U> Warriors and Paladins are kind enough to supply you with basic information.</DIV>
