<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Stuns <U>are</U> quite powerful. Your short parses instead of proving they are not proved the exact opposite and you sir are the ONLY reader that apparenlty doesn't appreciate it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Kahm at least puts things into perspective kinda, noting that stuns may be powerful in stunable content and even trivialize it, but they don't do anything vs. stun immune mobs. Warrior disciplines are quite powerful, but they are available for a few mobs and then we get 0 benefit from them for 10 minutes while they are refreshing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For goodness sake, move on from the fact that stuns even in your contrived example designed to show only a part of their usefullness outperform Defensive on a mob after mob after mob basis. We ALL know and have for quite awihile known that stuns are overwhelming vs. stunnable content sir.</DIV>	
