t appreciate it.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>Kahm at least puts things into perspective kinda, noting that stuns may be powerful in stunable content and even trivialize it, but they don't do anything vs. stun immune mobs. Warrior disciplines are quite powerful, but they are available for a few mobs and then we get 0 benefit from them for 10 minutes while they are refreshing.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>For goodness sake, move on from the fact that stuns even in your contrived example designed to show only a part of their usefullness outperform Defensive on a mob after mob after mob basis. We ALL know and have for quite awihile known that stuns are overwhelming vs. stunnable content sir.</DIV><br><hr></blockquote><br>"We ALL know and have for quite awihile known that stuns are overwhelming vs. stunnable content sir.", THAT is the issue, stereotypes, we need to examine them and figure out which make sense, which are bs, and which are half truths. Have you seen me write anywhere that paladins are inferior in low end stunnable content? I've argued much to the contrary in most cases. What surprised me, and apparently a large portion of the people on these boards judging from the insults and frantic attempts to pick apart the circumstances of the parse, is that the gap is so small. <br><br>As far as the SK discussed in the other thread. I didn't suggest that he was a ficticous character. I play on Xegony and I know of the existance of these people. I was refering to Frodlin's concern that the SK was out dps'ing and out mitigating him, which I believe can be attributed to contributing circumstances, thus "alleged"<br><br>Concerning the rest of your post, it's hard to pick apart your reasoning from the sarcasm and insults so I'm not going to try. The existance of this thread is a testament to the pre-determined opinions and political agendas displayed in this forum and the uneasiness created when someone challenges a stereotype. This isn't politics. Devs don't read these boards before determining what in game changes to make, so let's stop treating it as such.
