Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=7048#M7048">11</a> of 576
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 787 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Kahm wrote:</DIV>
<DIV>"Which leads to a&nbsp;question to ask Warriors, do they use these Discs in this manner, popping Defensive and Evasive when they refresh? Which is also a huge factor to consider when making such comparisons otherwise your just pen and paper theory that doesn't actually apply to the game."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The purpose of contrasting "stun mitigation" with Defensive was to provide a context by which it could be made crystal clear just how powerful "stun mitigation" really is. Over a long&nbsp;period of time "stun mitigation" significantly outperforms Warrior disciplines - but most of us already knew that.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Put your question another way. If Warriors are not "popping Defensive and Evasive when they refresh (and I don't - they are for cutting-edge named mobs in single-group content, always have been) then it's really:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>0 Warrior mitigation improvement by the use of spells and disciplines</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>vs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>13.1% Paladin mitigation improvent soloing by the use of "stun mitigation"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>and even more dramatic testement to how powerful "stun mitigation" is.</DIV>
<DIV>-------------</DIV>
<DIV>Offering an olive branch sir would be reading what was posted and reponding to it rather than simply dismissing it. I'll repeat myself as politely as I can:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>"Warrior innate mitigation includes "-1 DI"<STRONG> we are contrasting the beyond class <U>base</U> mitigation provided by "stun mitigation" and Defensive, not differences in innate mitigation.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A more accurate calculation would be:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3 minutes at 45% mitigation via Defensive (50% less the 5% innate warrior DI mitigation)</DIV>
<DIV>10 minutes at 0%</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10.38% mitigation of the DI potion of the damage only</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Warrior damage taken is found in the formula -</DIV>
<DIV>Damage = DB + ( ( RND(20)*DI) * 0.95)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Defensive is not a 45% reduction in melee damage taken, but <U>only in the DI contribution of the damage taken</U>. DB is never 0, and the average mitigation provided by Defensive is <U>always</U> less than 10.38%"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So the actual mitigation improvement by using "stun mitigation" vs Defensive over a 13 minute period would be:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Reduction beyond base mitigation&nbsp; - solo, melee only damage:</DIV>
<DIV>---------------------------------------------------------------------------------</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Paladin&nbsp;using "stun mitigation" per Maddar's parses: 13.1%</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Warrior&nbsp;using Defensive per BB's calcuation (13 minutes): less than 10.38%</STRONG> (does not account for DB damage)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Did anyone state a Hamstring discipline or ability would not have a level cap sir. It obviously would be subject to the same rules as root and snare as Kahm stated before you re-iterrated this concern.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hopefully a solution to Warrior's dependably stopping runners will appear on the Warrior Top Ten list and when it does, it will reflect ideas presented prior to your comments that were quite balanced and conciderate of classes who have snaring as an important secondary role. Just as we intended all along.</DIV></DIV>
