			>
			<DIV>Junky,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Because&nbsp;"-1 DI" is not a seperate Warriror ability it's built into us just as surely as any differences in mitigation tables, avoidance, dodge, block, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The question was percentage improvement over normal&nbsp;mitigation by using spells and abilities. That's what my calculation provided and that's what I believe parces would show for a Warriror not under Defensive vs. a Warrior under Defensive</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>(sortof, its far more complicated than that with&nbsp;things like high AC returning a lot of minimum hits which, since the DI contribution is already 1*DI aren't capable of further reduction because of Defensive. I think - scratches head.) </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The question of who mitigates more and by how much is a seperate question. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>---------------</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>By subject to the regular rules of root and snare, I of course was refering to the immune to changes in run speed rules, not the fact that Root (actually Paladins have a decent Root) might break early, etc.</DIV>	
