<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Maddar_Xegony wrote:<BR><EM>Frodlin, you're completely misrepresenting what I've said, to the point of boardering Battleblade's cutting of my sentence is half. <BR><BR>What you said: "1. That taking 0, 0, 0, 0, 350, 350, 760, 540 is more dangerous than 350, 350, 710, 500, 350, 350, 710, 500 "because it's spikey"<BR><BR>What I actually said: ""Spike damage" for the record can also mean that you're not hit for 8 or so seconds and then start taking <U>higher dps</U> than the tank getting constant damage would take. Your narrow definition is absurd."</EM></P>
<P>The reality is you don't take significantly higher DPS than warriors when you're not being hit, it's an absolute myth that you take a huge amount more damage when hit than warriors.&nbsp; That's the entire problem.&nbsp; Your mitigation curve looks strikingly similar to&nbsp;a warrior's mitigation curve, thus it's not dangerous spike damage, it's just the elimination of combat rounds.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><EM>- The implication being that both are taking the same dps over time</EM></P><EM></EM></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>But they are NOT taking the same DPS over time under ANY circumstance.&nbsp; You mitigate amazingly closely to warriors, and you can eliminate entire combat rounds.&nbsp; How on earth do you get "both are taking the same dps over time"?<BR><BR><EM>What you said: "that 13% avoidance (avoidance being 100% mitigation and elimination of all DB and DI damage) is something that is even remotely close to 5% mitigation and 1.5% avoidance"<BR><BR>What I actually said: "Mitigation from warrior discs and - 1DI(factoring in refresh times) &gt; mitigation from chain stunning, depending on the swing speed of the mob."</EM><BR><BR>But it's not, that's the entire point.... defensive does little to nothing in lower end content.&nbsp; Again, at least Kether was on the right track when he invoked evasive, although it's still not even remotely comparable, at LEAST it's avoidance vs. avoidance.&nbsp;&nbsp; </P>
<P>But just to make it crystal clear what you "said" so that you arent' able to whittle your way out of it, here's what YOU said..</P>
<P><STRONG><EM>You can't avoid this by throwing in the argument of avoidance versus mitigation. In an experience group setting there is absolutely positively zero difference in the long term.</EM></STRONG></P>
<P>There is an ENROMOUS difference in short term, long term, medium term, any kind of term you can come up with.</P>
<P><BR><BR><EM>You've succesfully driven another voice of reason from your forum /golf clap.</EM><BR></P>
<P>If you define "voice of reason" as someone who tries to&nbsp;put across&nbsp;that you determine the savings of stuns can be ascertained by slowed mobs, who doesnt' acknowledge that the most dangerous time of a fight (and most powerful time for a Paladin's stuns) is pre-slow, and of course in the enormous solo imbalance, or one who continues to call avoidance "mitigation", or&nbsp;say "<EM>In an experience group setting there is absolutely positively zero difference in the long term"</EM>&nbsp;&nbsp;talking about avoidance by eliminating melee rounds completely vs. getting hit for a minimum of DB+1DI when they're not even remotely close, then frankly, the "voice of reason" is speaking a language which isn't readily understood.<BR></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
