		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The voice of reason is pretty much everyone in this thread except Maddar.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The facts are:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<OL>
<LI>The higher your AC, the less effective Defensive becomes.</LI>
<LI>Stuns become more effective the more stuns you can stack on the mob.</LI>
<LI>Most exp groups don't hit hard and the average modal of the hits are between 5 and 9.</LI>
<LI>Defensive effectively halfs the modal (from 5-9 to 2.5-4.5).</LI>
<LI>The DI portion of the damage on most mobs in exp groups would mean each hit would be around 120 less damage.</LI>
<LI>You can not even begin to compare 120 less damage per hit to avoiding several rounds of 500 damage per hit or more.</LI>
<LI>You have either have a complete lack of understand of how combat in EQ works, or you are being purposefully dishonest.</LI></OL>
<P>The 8 percent comes from your calculation that Defensive is roughly equal to 15.xx percent less damage over 13 minutes average and factoring in that the 15.xx percent is ONLY applied to the DI portion.&nbsp; In most exp groups, the damage you take with current AC levels is roughly half DB damage and half DI damage.&nbsp; Defensive lowers DI by half which results in a 25 percent decrease in damage.&nbsp; When you factor this over 13 minutes, you get around 8 percent less.</P>
<P>Which is it?&nbsp; Are you purposefully being dishonest or do you lack the framework to understand why what you are saying is absurd?</P>	
