		" 
			>
			As I have said before, I am fine with taking more damage than a warrior.  Want to eliminate this 'unfairness' of stuns that causes variations in dps taken depending on ability utilization?  Fine.  You have my blessing to call for fixed tanking mods.  For every 100pts a warrior takes a paladin would take 115.  Stuns become 'interrupt only'.  Remove all stun immunities and level caps on the highest rank.  Differential softcaps go, varying overcap returns go, armor differentials go, avoidance skill gaps go, disciplines are matched in all parameters, etc...  That 15% penalty is always a 15% difference, never less and never more.<br><br>But this latest 'stuns are more overpowered than ever!' campaign is just plain tacky as I doubt the most vocal of the crowd would subscribe to such a universal tanking 'balance'.  Instead we have some three ring circle of ineptitude apparently working darn hard to prove their own ability to form a coherant argument.<br><br>The measure of an ability or a class in a group is how efficient and powerful their group is against content to bring them rewards.  Where warriors as a class are coming up short is the need for more efficient slow solo XP (fixed), and in the areas of shield utilization and post-rez endurance regen (both likely to be implemented).  Where paladins are coming up short is aggro at the higher end (both initial for CC, and sustained), and innate and level immunities for their stuns in a group setting (future unknown).  SKs are coming up short no where.	
		</td></tr>
