		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>The purpose of contrasting "stun mitigation" with Defensive was to provide a context by which it could be made crystal clear just how powerful "stun mitigation" really is. Over a long&nbsp;period of time "stun mitigation" significantly outperforms Warrior disciplines - but most of us already knew that.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Put your question another way. If Warriors are not "popping Defensive and Evasive when they refresh (and I don't - they are for cutting-edge named mobs in single-group content, always have been) then it's really:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>0 Warrior mitigation improvement by the use of spells and disciplines</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>vs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>13.1% Paladin mitigation improvent soloing by the use of "stun mitigation"</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Rather, um, misleading aren't you Battleblade? Now I for one fully acknowledge the practical benifits from stuns and the resulting Net Stun&nbsp;Damage Reduction Over Time&nbsp;(I'm going to use my own phrase for this <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> ), however you are glazing over a few things in you posts:</P>
<P>-You disciplines refresh at the beginning of use, meaning there is a 7 minute gap between uses, not a 10 minute gap. You stipulate a 13 minute period (10&nbsp; and 3) when in fact it would be a 10 minute period (7 and 3)</P>
<P>-You are ignoring other components of the Warrior survivability, you will take less damage per hit and avoid more hits then a Paladin outside of any discipline usage, so it's misleading to say you have "0 mitigation improvement" vs our Net Stun Damage Reduction Over Time</P>
<P>Yes, I agree a discrepency occurs due to our stuns vs lower end content. However that difference is far from being "overwhelming" or "overpowering" as some have described. Only a few relatively minor changes are needed to deal with any issue involved here, and keep in mind that conversely our stuns are ineffective on stun immune content, (for good reason) whcih severely hampers our effectiveness.&nbsp;(something that occurs throughout our career) This Net Stun Damage Reduction Over Time is of moot point value in stunnable content because we frankly do not need it to tank in most of that content.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
