		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>"Where warriors as a class are coming up short is the need for more efficient slow solo XP (fixed), and in the areas of shield utilization and post-rez endurance regen (both likely to be implemented). Where paladins are coming up short is aggro at the higher end (both initial for CC, and sustained), and innate and level immunities for their stuns in a group setting (future unknown). SKs are coming up short no where. "</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So smooth and so self-serving.</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>"Want to eliminate this 'unfairness' of stuns that causes variations in dps taken depending on ability utilization?"</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>No sir, I want mobs to have a recourse that once a stun lands, the mob is unaffected by any other stun for 10 seconds with weapon procs and augs altered to generate fixed hate despite this change and with Paladin aggro from stuns that actually stick to adjusted relfect the lower rate of casting.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There should be no need nor any advantage to chaining stuns - none.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>"more efficient slow solo XP (fixed)"</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Not fixed by a long shot. Have you used the potions Kether? While they beat nothing, I have played both a Paladin and and SK and I'm telling you truthfully - solo each one of these classes sir and the differences are profound. Or if you can't find a Warrior, just solo in ToSoRo for a couple of hours without casting a spell and relying on potions. Be sure to post how it went.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>"parity in big mob/named soloing"</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Ooops, missed that one big fella.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>"post-rez endurance regen"</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>And continuous endurance regen and some short duration/short refresh disciplines to spend that regenerating endurance on like say for example self-heals, group friendly utility, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>You forgot so-called utility</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Warriors are essentially Knights without utility in all single group content sir. We are interchangable as tanks (my classes intended strength) and both Knights retain overwhelmingly more powerful so-called "utility" (Paladins are Clerics lacking only CH and SK's are Tanks and FD pullers).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Where paladins are coming up short is aggro at the higher end (both initial for CC, and sustained)"</DIV>
<DIV>Bullocks <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> I'm actually in high end content Kether. What "high-level content" has&nbsp;Arete faced or that you have heard about where&nbsp;Paladin aggro is difficient?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I don't see any such difficiencies in the ability of Paladins in my guild when we kill Tunat, OOM, and Vishimtar and every single one of&nbsp; the&nbsp;mobs on the way to them and all of the flag content needed to reach those zones.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My guild uses Paladins and SK's and not Warriors excusively for MA's and addtanks because of their VASTLY superior short term aggro. And when I beat on a mob being tanked by a Knight, I do not switch to a low aggro setup and click off aggro buffs - I can not steal aggro from a Knight without using Taunt or AE Taunt sir and I have&nbsp;about as much aggro generating ability as a Warrrior can have.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Paladins have no sustained aggro difficiency at the high end either sir. You class is expected to have less sustained aggro than Warriors (and superior short term aggro). So what "high-level" mob precisely are you tanking or you have heard about a Paladin tanking where&nbsp;higher sustained aggro is required?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>(I'm looking at your Magelo) -&nbsp;Where's your aggro aug on that Hopebringer. Heck, concidering the ratio on that Hopebringer, why aren't you weilding a Blade of Disruption with a CS IV aug when you tank?? Wheres's your Symbol of the Planesmaster or</STRONG> <STRONG>Gloves of the Crimson Sigil? I assume you get an SK Voice of Thule buff.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>With a Magelo indicating&nbsp;0 effort on your part to generate aggro,&nbsp;you don't have any&nbsp;credibility at all in making these assertions.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Maintaining aggro discipline is everybody's job Kether. Paladins are not aggro kings intended to pull aggro off an overnuking Wizzy with a single gem click and hold aggro in an iron grip. </STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Mind you, like every Warrior I know, I support SoE:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1.&nbsp;Introducing an aggro weapon in high level content where these difficulties allegedly (I'm there and I've not once seen them)&nbsp;occur or perhaps altering Blade of Forgotten Faith to have a nice aggro proc instead of the not Tank appropriate Cleric proc or making sure such a weapon exists in the next expansion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. Making Anger 2 and 3 augs Knight usable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Altering Knight high level BP's to have&nbsp;Echo of Anger Effect instead of whatever non-tank focus effect they might have or introducing a new armor item in the next expanion with EoA.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Reducing how often Paladins have to click and are able to click stuns to maintain aggro.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But you don't, given my reading of your posts and looking at your Magelo, want reasonable change requiring effort on your part to obtain and hold aggro, you want snap-aggro on demand AND high sustainable aggro without effort.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SK's need utility to balance out the enormous advantage Paladins have with thier abilitiy to Res like a Cleric and Buff like a Cleric. They also need the ability to dependably stop gaters.</DIV></DIV>	
