Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&message.id=7098#M7098">25</a> of 576
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 624 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Battleblade-Xegony wrote:<BR>
<DIV>No sir, I want mobs to have a recourse that once a stun lands, the mob is unaffected by any other stun for 10 seconds with weapon procs and augs altered to generate fixed hate despite this change and with Paladin aggro from stuns that actually stick to adjusted relfect the lower rate of casting.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There should be no need nor any advantage to chaining stuns - none.</DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Sorry, While there is a discrepency caused by stuns, and I am agreeable that Warriors shold get boosts and tools where needed to alleviate this concern, I also fail to see evidence that Stuns are overpowering or overwhelming. There is no content that stuns trivialize, except&nbsp;when that content is already trivial.</P>
<P>This Nerf you propose is simply unneeded and unaccpetable and would adversely effect&nbsp;stuns far beyond addressing your concerns about the net damage being avoided by a Paladin in low end content. Not to mention adversely effect 4 other classes with stuns.</P>
<P>Sorry a better solution would be to give the Warriors a group friendly disc. similair to the new Knight disc that has a fast reuse, low endurance cost, shorter duration to match the mob's lifespan and no melee damage penalty. Not only does that alleviate the discrepency, but also offers Warriors a good Utility tool, (not to mention it would work against unstunnable content as well where this issue doesn't occur)</P>
<P>To be frank, I suspect you are just trying to grab more power and find an excuse for Nerfage. really "Paladins are Clerics lacking only CH"?&nbsp; Sorry your exagerating the issues and ignoring Warrior advantages too much. While both sides can be guilty of this, and there are issues, they aren't resolved by rhetorical nonsense either.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>07-06-2005</span> <span class=time_text>11:29 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
